00:00:02.836 --> 00:00:06.906
Namaskar! Welcome to Nishmadhulika.com

00:00:07.382 --> 00:00:14.351
Today we will make Thickened milk and peas sabzi.
It is very tasty and rich.

00:00:14.867 --> 00:00:29.109
We can make this for a party or for a special occasion or whenever
you feel like eating something special then you can make it.

00:00:29.758 --> 00:00:32.945
Let's start making the sabzi.

00:00:33.828 --> 00:00:36.890
1 cup frozen peas.

00:00:37.398 --> 00:00:44.125
1 cup or 200 grams thickened milk.

00:00:45.039 --> 00:00:48.640
3 /200 grams tomatoes.

00:00:49.148 --> 00:00:50.304
2 green chillies.

00:00:51.195 --> 00:00:53.406
2-3 tbsp green coriander.

00:00:53.922 --> 00:00:55.828
2 tbsp ghee.

00:00:56.352 --> 00:00:58.500
½ tsp Ginger paste.

00:00:58.906 --> 00:01:00.859
½ tsp cumin seeds.

00:01:01.188 --> 00:01:03.625
¼ tsp mixed spices.

00:01:03.945 --> 00:01:06.421
½ turmeric powder.

00:01:06.766 --> 00:01:09.226
¼ tsp Red chilli powder.

00:01:09.828 --> 00:01:11.968
½ tsp Anise seed powder.

00:01:12.453 --> 00:01:14.578
1 tsp coriander powder.

00:01:14.883 --> 00:01:19.546
¾ tsp salt (according to your taste)

00:01:20.343 --> 00:01:28.820
Firstly we will grind tomatoes and green chillies.

00:01:29.155 --> 00:01:41.226
Cut the tomatoes and green chillies so that it will be easily grinded.

00:01:51.398 --> 00:01:57.585
Now grind it. Heat the pan and put ghee.

00:02:03.531 --> 00:02:31.282
Add cumin seeds, turmeric powder, ginger paste, coriander powder,
anise seed powder and then add the grinded tomato and green chillies.

00:02:35.587 --> 00:02:44.079
Add red chilli powder. Stir it till the oil separates from the masala.

00:02:46.493 --> 00:02:52.493
The oil has separated. Now add the green peas.

00:02:53.595 --> 00:03:08.326
These are frozen peas so they are half boiled. If you are taking fresh
peas then boil in the water for 2-3 minutes and take the half boiled peas.

00:03:08.858 --> 00:03:22.578
Now add 2-3 tbsp water and cook it in low flame for 3-4 minutes.
So, that the spices are mixed with the peas.

00:03:23.335 --> 00:03:33.539
Till then we will crumble the thickened milk with a spoon.

00:03:37.438 --> 00:03:39.539
We have crumbled it.

00:03:40.883 --> 00:03:49.961
4 minutes have passes now we will add the
crumbled thickened milk in the sabzi.

00:03:56.172 --> 00:04:00.969
Stir it continuously and cook it for 2-3 minutes.

00:04:15.797 --> 00:04:28.753
It's done now I can smell the fragrance of it. Now add
salt, mixed spices and a little coriander and mix it.

00:04:31.487 --> 00:04:38.355
If you want gravy then add some water according to yourself.

00:04:39.425 --> 00:04:46.347
The sabzi is ready. Turn off the stove. Take it out in a bowl.

00:04:52.355 --> 00:04:55.730
Garnish with fresh coriander.

00:04:57.519 --> 00:05:01.644
Peas and thickened milk sabzi is ready.

00:05:02.018 --> 00:05:06.503
It has come out very nice and this can serve upto 4-5 people.

00:05:07.269 --> 00:05:14.940
You can serve it as a side dish with chapatti, paranthas or rice.

00:05:15.363 --> 00:05:22.651
You can make your peas and thickened milk's sabzi, eat it and enjoy it.
